{"TopicId":192245,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Anyway to disable all Kerbin ground relays?","CreatedByName":"Evernow","CreatedById":195050,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-08T19:34:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Evernow","CreatedById":195050,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-08T19:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello there!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am planning out a way to have a relay system to be able to communicate through all of Kerbin, and for immersion sake, is there a way to disable all the ground relays, so the only way to communicate with the space center would be to have a relay in orbit (multiple that is) relaying you to the space center?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-08T20:57:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can do that in the difficulty settings menu (I\u0027m playing another career game, and this is one of my \u0022immersion\u0022 settings).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did set up my relay network as per this guide (though I used RA-100 antennas for everything):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-08T20:59:00Z\u0022 title=\u002203/08/2020 08:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 8, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Evernow","CreatedById":195050,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-08T21:28:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223753820\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583701033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can do that in the difficulty settings menu (I\u0027m playing another career game, and this is one of my \u0022immersion\u0022 settings).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did set up my relay network as per this guide (though I used RA-100 antennas for everything):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! Starting a new game now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-08T22:32:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTurn off the other launch locations as well, as they\u0027ll provide communications too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T09:48:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223753852\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583706722\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTurn off the other launch locations as well, as they\u0027ll provide communications too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... and a fairly recent change (in 1.9.?) actually disables their ground stations for that case. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Before that the other launch locations were still working as ground stations, no matter what.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T13:00:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223753820\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583701033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can do that in the difficulty settings menu (I\u0027m playing another career game, and this is one of my \u0022immersion\u0022 settings).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did set up my relay network as per this guide (though I used RA-100 antennas for everything):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a bit of of an overkill to use RA-2 relays for the lower Kerbin ring. I found that a ring of quad HG-5 satellites at 500 km altitude is enough for low-orbit communications.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T13:25:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754029\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583758839\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fraktal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Fraktal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a bit of of an overkill\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s exactly why I use RA-100 for all relay satellites \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EBecause I can, and in case of doubt: moar booster \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T14:32:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that case, how do you launch highly un-aerodynamic payloads too large to fit into a fairing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T14:53:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThree sat units (probe core, RA-100, solar panels, reaction wheel, tank, engine) do fit fine in a 3.75m fairing \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-09T14:54:35Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2020 02:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T15:27:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about four RA-2 satellites mounted on the end of girders in an X shape for a\u00A0visually pleasing ground-based relay?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T15:57:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForm follows function, or: KISS (Keep It Simple and Stupid)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot10-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-20\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022294.61\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u0022260\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/kBjTsvY/screenshot10-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-2020-03-09-16-53-34.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not known for building any elegant designed rockets, I just want it to work \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-09T17:27:03Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2020 05:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T17:01:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223753981\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583747300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... and a fairly recent change (in 1.9.?) actually disables their ground stations for that case. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Before that the other launch locations were still working as ground stations, no matter what.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMust be 1.9.1\u00A0because I didn\u2019t notice it in 1.9\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will check it out, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T17:11:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583773286\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMust be 1.9.1\u00A0because I didn\u2019t notice it in 1.9\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be. I only tested in 1.9.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T19:45:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583773879\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be. I only tested in 1.9.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOur two observation cases as a Venn diagram: O O\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T22:17:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754125\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583769463\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForm follows function, or: KISS (Keep It Simple and Stupid)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/kBjTsvY/screenshot10-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-2020-03-09-16-53-34.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot10-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-20\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022294.61\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u0022260\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/kBjTsvY/screenshot10-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-2020-03-09-16-53-34.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not known for building any elegant designed rockets, I just want it to work \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t know you could stack stuff inside fairings like that\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u00A0Must try this!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cavscout74","CreatedById":181783,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-09T22:26:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583792265\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199902\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jimmymcgoochie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, jimmymcgoochie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t know you could stack stuff inside fairings like that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the part window for the fairings, there is an option \u0022Enable interstage nodes\u0022 or something like that.\u00A0 Turn it on to stack multiple items inside the fairing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-10T01:40:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou still need to use decouplers between the interstage node and the payload, though. Few versions ago there was an update that keeps interstage nodes attached even after the fairing is popped open.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-10T05:50:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754385\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583804409\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fraktal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Fraktal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFew versions ago there was an update that keeps interstage nodes attached even after the fairing is popped open.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t remember it being different than it is now, and how would I put the three relay satellites into a triangular formation if they wouldn\u0027t be attached to the interstage nodes after the fairing has been opened?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can see the decouplers too in my screenshot, plus the little Okto directly put on the fairing below the decoupler there. Together with the two batteries, it allows me, after deploying the relay satellites, to let the carrier rocket crash into the CB, avoiding any space junk.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-10T05:52:31Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2020 05:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-10T18:22:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192245\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583819441\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t remember it being different than it is now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/21915\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EIt\u0027s a bug that appeared in 1.7 and still hasn\u0027t been fixed.\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0If the fairing is between the root part (or\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eis\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0the root part) and the interstage node, the node won\u0027t detach when the fairing opens. Makes it impossible to launch multiple satellites in one go without having to waste payload mass on decouplers to detach the sats from what should be thin air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-10T18:28:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh? Ohkay...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remember placing my relays in my old career before 1.7., and placing my relays in 1.8.1, never noticed any difference.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWeird.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}